The paper discusses the application of operations research techniques to power network optimization problems, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). The development of data-driven models for missing network operation constraints involves machine learning and artificial intelligence techniques (cs.AI, cs.LG). The paper also deals with network optimization and power flow, which are relevant to the categories of networked systems (cs.NE) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
